data.Generated_facility_notes_full_text: The state does not provide facility-level data.
data.Public_Notes:
Nebraska does not report COVID-19 data related to long-term-care facilities on their dashboard. COVID Tracking Project puts long-term-care data in the Lumped or Other category in our dataset. Nebraska would infrequently email long-term-care facility data to COVID Tracking Project. Nebraska reports cumulative data, not outbreak. Nebraska does not provide facility-level data. Nebraska reports staff and resident cases and staff and resident deaths separately. 

Nebraska provides cumulative totals for resident and staff cases and resident and staff deaths and number of facilities with a case. 

Nebraska does not report outbreak data.

Nebraska does not report facility-level data.

Long-term-care reporting has occurred in press conferences. The last known update was June 15, 2020. After June 15, 2020, CTP only received updated information via email from state officials. Updates were infrequent, resulting in weeks of data being carried over.
